This paper discusses a security vulnerability in a personalized insurance mechanism used by auto insurance companies, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). The proposed defense mechanism involves the use of statistical models and data collection from the physical world, which could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the evaluation of the defense mechanism involves testing its effectiveness in the real world, which could be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI).
